@node main "TB4.0 Help"

 @{" TB4.0 Guide " link "TB4.0-Guide/MAIN" 0}

 The new interface may look a little complex when compared to the old one.
 Once you konw you know the basics you will discover how easy to use TB4.0
 accually is.

 @{" The Buttons " link b1} - Explains what each button does.
 @{" The Menus   " link m1} - Explains what each meny item does.

@ENDNODE

@node b1 "The Buttons"

 There are 5 buttons below the title bar of the TB4.0 window.  @{" Show Me " link "MODS/BPIC1.IFF/MAIN"}

 Below the numbers are represented as numbers.

 [@{fg shine}1@{fg text}][@{fg shine}2@{fg text}][@{fg shine}3@{fg text}][@{fg shine}4@{fg text}][@{fg shine}5@{fg text}]

 @{fg shine}1@{fg text} @{" New File  " link b2} - Create a new file.
 @{fg shine}2@{fg text} @{" Load File " link b3} - Load a TB file.
 @{fg shine}3@{fg text} @{" Save File " link b4} - Save a TB file.
 @{fg shine}4@{fg text} @{" Edit File " link b5} - Edit file in memory.
 @{fg shine}5@{fg text} @{" Help      " link b6} - View on-line help.

 @{" Contents " link main}

@endnode


@node b2 "New File"

 This opens the New File window and let you create a new file.

 Press OK      to accept the file.
 Press Cancel  to not create a new file.

 Note - The file is created in memory and will be lost if you quit TB4.0
        You must @{" save " link b4} the file if you want to keep it.
        New will also overwrite any information that is already in memory.

 The Fields:-

 Dialling Code - EG 01772
        Number - EG 12345
          Name - EG Stuart
       Surname - EG Kelly
       Address - EG 8 Squires Wood
          Area - EG Fulwood
     Town/City - EG Preston
     Post Code - EG PR2 9QA
        E-Mail - EG stuart@dkelly1.demon.co.uk
        Moblie - EG None
           Fax - EG None

 @{" The Buttons " link b1}

@endnode


@node b3 "Load File"

 Load a file from disk.  Just select the file to load and press OK.

 Loading a file will overwrite ALL information stored in memory.
 Unsaved data can NOT be recovered.

 @{" The Buttons " link b1}
 @{" The Menus   " link m1}

@endnode


@node b4 "Save File"

 Note - This only works if you have a file in memory.

 Save a file to disk.  Just select where to save it and press OK.

 TB4.0 will generate a filename for you. eg - surname-name.TB
 This helps to keep files in surname order.

 Just change the filename if you don't want it like this.

 @{" The Buttons " link b1}
 @{" The Menus   " link m1}

@endnode


@node b5 "Edit File"

 Note - This only works if you have a file in memory.

 Edit the current file in memory.  Edit works in the same way as @{" New " link b2}.

 Press OK     to accept changes.
 Press Cancel to ignore canges.

 @{" The Buttons " link b1}
 @{" The Menus   " link m1}

@endnode


